.TH "fscrypt_fname_encrypt" 9 "fscrypt_fname_encrypt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fscrypt_fname_encrypt \- encrypt a filename
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fscrypt_fname_encrypt
.BI "(const struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "const struct qstr *iname "  ","
.BI "u8 *out "  ","
.BI "unsigned int olen "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
inode of the parent directory (for regular filenames)
or of the symlink (for symlink targets)
.IP "iname" 12
the filename to encrypt
.IP "out" 12
(output) the encrypted filename
.IP "olen" 12
size of the encrypted filename.  It must be at least \fIiname->len\fP.
Any extra space is filled with NUL padding before encryption.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno on failure
